<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2008-03-12</DATELINE><TITLE>Hemagglutinating Encephalomyelitis Coronavirus Infection in Pigs, Argentina</TITLE><BODY>We describe an outbreak of vomiting, wasting, and encephalomyelitis syndrome in piglets in Argentina, caused by porcine hemagglutinating encephalomyelitis coronavirus (PHE-CoV) infection. Diagnosis was made by epidemiologic factors, pathologic features, immunohistochemistry, reverse transcriptionâ€“PCR, and genomic sequencing. This study documents PHE-CoV infection in South America.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>